sql:
SELECT DISTINCT l.location_desc
FROM health_data hd
INNER JOIN locations l ON hd.location_id = l.location_id;

external_knowledge:
- Age-adjusted rates are rates that have been adjusted to account for differences in population age distribution across different locations, allowing for fairer comparisons; 
- Spatially smoothed rates are rates that have been adjusted to account for spatial autocorrelation, reducing the impact of extreme values; 
- 3-year average rate is the average rate over a 3-year period, providing a more stable estimate of the mortality rate; 
- Cardiovascular disease mortality rates refer to the number of deaths due to cardiovascular diseases per unit of population per year.

